    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.KeyListener, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants

    public class SAFSMonitorFrame
extends javax.swing.JFrame
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.KeyListener
    A class to monitor and potentially abort running SAFS tests. This class leverages functionality built into the SAFS DefaultDriver. The default driver monitors the SAFSVARS variables:
      'SAFS_DRIVER_CONTROL'
      'SAFS_DRIVER_CONTROL_POF'
    The driver can be shutdown by setting 'SAFS_DRIVER_CONTROL' to 'SHUTDOWN_HOOK'.
    The driver can Pause On Failure by setting 'SAFS_DRIVER_CONTROL_POF' to 'ON'.

      • shownOnFrontWhenPause

        public static boolean shownOnFrontWhenPause
        If shownOnFrontWhenPause is true, the monitor window will be shown on top when test state is PAUSE, the monitor will be at back when state is not PAUSE. Otherwise, the monitor will stay at back whatever the test state is.
